<li class="faq-item section">
<div class="topic collapsed at-action" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapsefaq_1758767980" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapsefaq_1758767980" data-tag="|NVR|" data-at-module="faq_list::click::How to Use N+1 Hot Spare in NVR">How to Use N+1 Hot Spare in NVR</div>
<div class="content-section collapse" id="collapsefaq_1758767980" data-parent="#faqAccordionfaq_container_copy">
    <div class="description hiknow-rte"><p>N+1 hot spare function is used for backup NVR. The maximum of ‘N’ is 32. </p>
<p>Note: This function is now supported by DS-9600NI-I series and DS-96000NI-I series NVR.</p>
</div>
    <ul class="assets-list">
        
        <li>
            <a class="asset at-action" href="https://www.tongfangbms.com/content/dam/tongfang/en/support/how-to/how-to-document/nvr/How-to-Use-N1-Hot-Spare-in-NVR.pdf" style="background-image:url('https://www.tongfangbms.com/content/dam/tongfang/en/marketing/icons/navigation-icons/document.svg')" target="_blank" data-at-module="faq_list::How to Use N+1 Hot Spare in NVR::How-to-Use-N1-Hot-Spare-in-NVR.pdf">How-to-Use-N1-Hot-Spare-in-NVR.pdf</a>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
</li>
<li class="faq-item section">
<div class="topic collapsed at-action" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapsefaq_599075692" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapsefaq_599075692" data-tag="|NVR|" data-at-module="faq_list::click::How to Watch Smart Playback in NVR">How to Watch Smart Playback in NVR</div>
<div class="content-section collapse" id="collapsefaq_599075692" data-parent="#faqAccordionfaq_container_copy">
    <div class="description hiknow-rte"><p>The smart playback function provides an easy way to get through the less effective information. When you select the smart playback mode, the system will analyze the video containing the motion or VCA information. It will mark it with red color and play it in normal speed, while the video without motion will be played in the 16-time speed（the speed function can be configurable, -E/-Q is not supported）. The smart playback rules and areas are configurable. </p>
<p>Note: This speed function is now supported by almost all -K/-I/-super I series NVR.</p>
</div>
    <ul class="assets-list">
        
        <li>
            <a class="asset at-action" href="https://www.tongfangbms.com/content/dam/tongfang/en/support/how-to/how-to-document/nvr/How-to-Watch-Smart-Playback-in-NVR.pdf" style="background-image:url('https://www.tongfangbms.com/content/dam/tongfang/en/marketing/icons/navigation-icons/document.svg')" target="_blank" data-at-module="faq_list::How to Watch Smart Playback in NVR::How-to-Watch-Smart-Playback-in-NVR.pdf">How-to-Watch-Smart-Playback-in-NVR.pdf</a>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
</li>
<li class="faq-item section">
<div class="topic collapsed at-action" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapsefaq_1899456870" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapsefaq_1899456870" data-tag="|NVR|" data-at-module="faq_list::click::How to Use NVR Cloud Storage Function">How to Use NVR Cloud Storage Function</div>
<div class="content-section collapse" id="collapsefaq_1899456870" data-parent="#faqAccordionfaq_container_copy">
    <div class="description hiknow-rte"><p>Note:</p>
<p>1:There are two different ways to use NVR cloud storage function： NVR as Storage Server: It can be added to other HCP or NVRs. NVR as Client End: You can add Cloud Storage Server to the client NVR, such as Hikvision cloud 2.0 or another NVR (which is set as storage server). </p>
<p>2：For NVR Cloud Storage Function, the protocol we use is Hikvision Cloud 2.0, and it only support Hikvision Cloud 2.0. The 3rd party cloud storage services such as Google Cloud, Baidu Cloud and Ali Cloud are not supported. </p>
<p>3：It only supports the storage of alarm pictures and does not support any video or data. </p>
</div>
    <ul class="assets-list">
        
        <li>
            <a class="asset at-action" href="https://www.tongfangbms.com/content/dam/tongfang/en/support/how-to/how-to-document/nvr/How-to-use-NVR-Cloud-Storage-Function.pdf" style="background-image:url('https://www.tongfangbms.com/content/dam/tongfang/en/marketing/icons/navigation-icons/document.svg')" target="_blank" data-at-module="faq_list::How to Use NVR Cloud Storage Function::How-to-use-NVR-Cloud-Storage-Function.pdf">How-to-use-NVR-Cloud-Storage-Function.pdf</a>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
</li>
<li class="faq-item section">
<div class="topic collapsed at-action" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapsefaq_889061206" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapsefaq_889061206" data-tag="|NVR|" data-at-module="faq_list::click::How to Use HTTPS Function of NVR">How to Use HTTPS Function of NVR</div>
<div class="content-section collapse" id="collapsefaq_889061206" data-parent="#faqAccordionfaq_container_copy">
    <div class="description hiknow-rte"><p>The function of HTTPS ensures the secure access of web services by adding digital signature certificate authentication. All series of NVRs support HTTPS function. This article takes k series NVR (DS-7608NI-K2 v4.30.061 build 210313) as an example to introduce how to use HTTPS function.</p>
</div>
    <ul class="assets-list">
        
        <li>
            <a class="asset at-action" href="https://www.tongfangbms.com/content/dam/tongfang/en/support/how-to/how-to-document/nvr/How-to-Use-HTTPS-Function-of-NVR.pdf" style="background-image:url('https://www.tongfangbms.com/content/dam/tongfang/en/marketing/icons/navigation-icons/document.svg')" target="_blank" data-at-module="faq_list::How to Use HTTPS Function of NVR::How-to-Use-HTTPS-Function-of-NVR.pdf">How-to-Use-HTTPS-Function-of-NVR.pdf</a>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
</li>
<li class="faq-item section">
<div class="topic collapsed at-action" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapsefaq_1137688755" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapsefaq_1137688755" data-tag="|TURBO HD CAMERA|" data-at-module="faq_list::click::How to Switch Signal Output of Four in one Analog Camera">How to Switch Signal Output of Four in one Analog Camera</div>
<div class="content-section collapse" id="collapsefaq_1137688755" data-parent="#faqAccordionfaq_container_copy">
    <div class="description hiknow-rte"><p>1. Open the waterproof cap of the switch button. </p>
<p>2. Press and hold the switch button. 5s later, the image will be no video because the camera is rebooting and do not loosen the button when the camera is rebooting.</p>
<p>3. Wait 2s after the image is stable again and then loosen the button (Do not loosen the button as soon as the image is normal). </p>
</div>
    <ul class="assets-list">
        
        <li>
            <a class="asset at-action" href="https://www.tongfangbms.com/content/dam/tongfang/en/support/how-to/how-to-document/turbo-hd-cameras/How-to-Switch-Signal-Output-of-Four-in-one-Analog-Camera.pdf" style="background-image:url('https://www.tongfangbms.com/content/dam/tongfang/en/marketing/icons/navigation-icons/document.svg')" target="_blank" data-at-module="faq_list::How to Switch Signal Output of Four in one Analog Camera::How-to-Switch-Signal-Output-of-Four-in-one-Analog-Camera.pdf">How-to-Switch-Signal-Output-of-Four-in-one-Analog-Camera.pdf</a>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
</li>
<li class="faq-item section">
